{"cursor":"14505","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\n\nIn phonetics, a 'stop', also known as a 'plosive', is an 'oral [[occlusive]]', a\nconsonant in which the vocal tract is blocked so that all airflow ceases. The\nocclusion may be done with the tongue (blade , , or body , ), lips (, ), or\nglottis (). Stops contrast with nasals, where the vocal tract is blocked but\nairflow continues through the nose, as in and , and with fricatives, where\npartial occlusion impedes but does not block airflow in the vocal tract.\n","linknr":625,"url":"Release_(phonetics)","recorded":1362478025,"links":67,"instances":["phonetics"],"pdf":[],"categories":["Plosives|"],"headings":["Terminology","Common stops","Articulation","Classification","Examples","See also","References","External links"],"image":["//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8a/Loudspeaker.svg/11px-Loudspeaker.svg.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/4f/Blank_vowel_trapezoid.svg/320px-Blank_vowel_trapezoid.svg.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8a/Loudspeaker.svg/11px-Loudspeaker.svg.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/vector/images/search-ltr.png?303-4","//bits.wikimedia.org/images/wikimedia-button.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/poweredby_mediawiki_88x31.png"],"tags":[["contour","phonetics"]],"members":["contour"],"related":["Phonetics","Consonant","Airstream_mechanism","Nasal_occlusive","Fricatives","Oral_consonant","Pulmonic_consonant","Ejective_consonant","Implosive_consonant","Glottal_stop","No_audible_release","Ancient_Greek","Latin","Dionysius_Thrax","Samoan_language","Coronal_consonant","Iroquoian","Iroquoian","Cherokee","Labial_consonant","Classical_Japanese","Classical_Arabic","Proto-Celtic_language","Samoan_language","Velar_consonant","Niâ€˜ihau","Hawaiian_language","Malay_language","Vietnamese_language","Nasal_release","No_audible_release","Affricate_consonant","Fricative_consonant","Contour_(pho